{"word":"βρέφος","slug":"βρέφος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>βρέφος, ους, τό</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> complex; ‘fetus’ (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Hom.\">Hom.</a>), then ‘newborn child’]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘unborn offspring’, <b><i>fetus, baby</i> <a href='B:490 1:41'>Lk 1:41</a>, <a href='B:490 1:44'>44</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘newborn or very young child’, <b><i>infant, baby</i> <a href='B:490 2:12'>Lk 2:12</a>, <a href='B:490 2:16'>16</a>; <a href='B:490 18:15'>18:15</a>; <a href='B:510 7:19'>Ac 7:19</a>;</b> in imagery <b><a href='B:670 2:2'>1 Pt 2:2</a>.—</b><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀπὸ\">ἀπὸ</a> βρέφους <i>from</i> <i>infancy</i> <b><a href='B:620 3:15'>2 Ti 3:15</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:βραχύς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:βρέχω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}